OL,3,CThe Terracotta Army showcases the
OL,4,Cartistry of more than 2,000 years ago
OL,6,FEven without the exclusive access
OL,7,Fgiven to Her Majesty, we were able to
OL,8,Ftake in the astonishing skill that
OL,9,Fwent into crafting each figure. One of
OL,10,Fthe most striking things about the
OL,11,Fwarriors when you see them up close is
OL,12,Fnoticing that no two faces are the
OL,13,Fsame.
OL,15,FEach stone soldier was given his own
OL,16,Fdistinct features. They have different
OL,17,Fnoses, hairstyles, eyebrows, and
OL,18,Fcheekbones, and centuries later it
OL,19,Fstill gives them a lifelike quality.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/13
